myQoSMIB.name: myQoSMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

myQoSMIB.description: This module defines my QoS(Policy-Based Quality of Service) mibs.

myPriorityTrafficClassNum.name: myPriorityTrafficClassNum
myPriorityTrafficClassNum.description: Number of the traffic class the priority can mapping to. Traffic class is a number in the range (1..myPriorityTrafficClassNum)

myPriorityClassNum.name: myPriorityClassNum
myPriorityClassNum.description: Number of the priority class. The range of Priority class is (0..(myPriorityClassNum-1))

myPriorityDscpMaxValue.name: myPriorityDscpMaxValue
myPriorityDscpMaxValue.description: max value of the dscp in system.

myTrafficClassTable.name: myTrafficClassTable
myTrafficClassTable.description: A table mapping evaluated User Priority to Traffic Class, for forwarding by the bridge. Traffic class is a number in the range (1..myPriorityTrafficClassNum).

myTrafficClassEntry.name: myTrafficClassEntry
myTrafficClassEntry.description: User Priority to Traffic Class mapping.

myTrafficClassPriority.name: myTrafficClassPriority
myTrafficClassPriority.description: The Priority value determined for the received frame. This value is equivalent to the priority indicated in the tagged frame received, or one of the evaluated priorities, determined according to the media-type. For untagged frames received from Ethernet media, this value is equal to the myPortDefaultUserPriority value for the ingress port. For untagged frames received from non-Ethernet media, this value is equal to the myRegenUserPriority value for the ingress port and media-specific user priority. This value is in the range(0..(myPriorityClassNum-1))

myTrafficClass.name: myTrafficClass
myTrafficClass.description: The Traffic Class the received frame is mapped to, Its value ranges between 0 and the value of the object myPriorityTrafficClass - 1. The priority is higher if this value is bigger.

myPriorityToDscp.name: myPriorityToDscp
myPriorityToDscp.description: Dscp value of priority mapping to.

myDscpClassTable.name: myDscpClassTable
myDscpClassTable.description: A table mapping evaluated dscp to priority.

myDscpClassEntry.name: myDscpClassEntry
myDscpClassEntry.description: A entry mapping evaluated dscp to priority.

myDscpClass.name: myDscpClass
myDscpClass.description: Dscp value.This value is even number in 0 between62

myDscpTrafficClassPriority.name: myDscpTrafficClassPriority
myDscpTrafficClassPriority.description: The priority which dscp value mapped to. This value is in the range(0..(myPriorityClassNum-1))

myPriorityTrafficClassOperMode.name: myPriorityTrafficClassOperMode
myPriorityTrafficClassOperMode.description: The global arithmetic type which the priority traffic class use.

myPriorityBandWidth.name: myPriorityBandWidth
myPriorityBandWidth.description: The global weight setting for every queue Each octet indicate a traffic class queue in the range(1..255) ,first octet indicate first queue. The string length equal to myPriorityTrafficClassNum.

myIfPriorityTable.name: myIfPriorityTable
myIfPriorityTable.description: A table that contains information about every interface

myIfPriorityEntry.name: myIfPriorityEntry
myIfPriorityEntry.description: A list of Default User Priorities for each interface.

myIfPriority.name: myIfPriority
myIfPriority.description: The default ingress User Priority for this interface. This value is in the range (0..(myPriorityClassNum-1))

myIfPriTrafficClassOperMode.name: myIfPriTrafficClassOperMode
myIfPriTrafficClassOperMode.description: The arithmetic type which the priority traffic class use in this interface.

myIfPriorityBandwidth.name: myIfPriorityBandwidth
myIfPriorityBandwidth.description: The weight of every queue on a interface. Each octet indicate a traffic class queue in the range(1..255) ,first octet indicate first queue. The string length equal to myPriorityTrafficClassNum.

myIfPriorityQosTrustMode.name: myIfPriorityQosTrustMode
myIfPriorityQosTrustMode.description: QoS trust mode for this interface.

myIpPreClassTable.name: myIpPreClassTable
myIpPreClassTable.description: A table mapping ip precedence to dscp value.

myIpPreClassPriority.name: myIpPreClassPriority
myIpPreClassPriority.description: The Ip precedence value determined for the received frame.

myIpPreToDscp.name: myIpPreToDscp
myIpPreToDscp.description: Dscp value of priority mapping to.

myIfRateLimitTable.name: myIfRateLimitTable
myIfRateLimitTable.description: list of rate limit interface objects.

myIfRateLimitInMaxBandWidth.name: myIfRateLimitInMaxBandWidth
myIfRateLimitInMaxBandWidth.description: Input maximum bandwidth of in units of kbps. 0 indicate that bandwidth will be not limitted.

myIfRateLimitInBurstFlowLimit.name: myIfRateLimitInBurstFlowLimit
myIfRateLimitInBurstFlowLimit.description: Input limit of burst traffic in units of byte. 0 indicate that burst traffic will be not limitted.

myIfRateLimitOutMaxBandWidth.name: myIfRateLimitOutMaxBandWidth
myIfRateLimitOutMaxBandWidth.description: Ouput maximum bandwidth of in units of kbps. 0 indicate that bandwidth will be not limitted.

myIfRateLimitOutBurstFlowLimit.name: myIfRateLimitOutBurstFlowLimit
myIfRateLimitOutBurstFlowLimit.description: Ouput limit of burst traffic in units of byte. 0 indicate that burst traffic will be not limitted.

myQoSTrafficClassTable.name: myQoSTrafficClassTable
myQoSTrafficClassTable.description: A table of Qos traffic classification entries.

myQoSTrafficClassEntry.name: myQoSTrafficClassEntry
myQoSTrafficClassEntry.description: QoS traffic classification entry.Every valid QoS traffic classification entry need make use of a MyAclEntry which myAclFlowAction is 'permit'.

myQosClassMapName.name: myQosClassMapName
myQosClassMapName.description: Name of this QoS class map.This value is unique for every entry. When this string be used as an index,Value of a sub-identifier equal ASCII value of corresponding character(first sub-identifier corresponds first character of string). The number of sub-identifiers of this string must be 32,If length of string is less than 32 the sub-identifier(0x0) will be filled in tail.

myQosClassAclName.name: myQosClassAclName
myQosClassAclName.description: Access list name of this class map match.Null indicate that this class map doesn't match any acl

myQosClassMapEntryStatus.name: myQosClassMapEntryStatus
myQosClassMapEntryStatus.description: Status of this entry, set this object to valid will creat a class map entry, and set its value to invalid will delete this entry.

myQoSPoliceMapTable.name: myQoSPoliceMapTable
myQoSPoliceMapTable.description: A table of Qos police map entries.

myQosPoliceMapName.name: myQosPoliceMapName
myQosPoliceMapName.description: Name of this QoS police map. When this string be used as an index,Value of a sub-identifier equal ASCII value of corresponding character(first sub-identifier corresponds first character of string). The number of sub-identifiers of this string must be 32,If length of string is less than 32 the sub-identifier(0x0) will be filled in tail.

myQosPoliceMapEntryStatus.name: myQosPoliceMapEntryStatus
myQosPoliceMapEntryStatus.description: Status of this entry, set this object to valid will creat a entry, and set its value to invalid will delete this entry.

myQoSPoliceMapConfTable.name: myQoSPoliceMapConfTable
myQoSPoliceMapConfTable.description: A table of Qos police map config entries.

myQoSPoliceCfgPoliceMapName.name: myQoSPoliceCfgPoliceMapName
myQoSPoliceCfgPoliceMapName.description: Name of this QoS police map. When this string be used as an index,Value of a sub-identifier equal ASCII value of corresponding character(first sub-identifier corresponds first character of string). The number of sub-identifiers of this string must be 32,If length of string is less than 32 the sub-identifier(0x0) will be filled in tail.

myQoSPoliceCfgClassMapName.name: myQoSPoliceCfgClassMapName
myQoSPoliceCfgClassMapName.description: A QoS class map name of this police map match. When this string be used as an index,Value of a sub-identifier equal ASCII value of corresponding character(first sub-identifier corresponds first character of string). The number of sub-identifiers of this string must be 32,If length of string is less than 32 the sub-identifier(0x0) will be filled in tail.

myQoSPoliceMapConfMaxBandWidth.name: myQoSPoliceMapConfMaxBandWidth
myQoSPoliceMapConfMaxBandWidth.description: Maximum bandwidth of this traffic classification in units of bps. If the Maximum bandwidth is greater than the maximum value reportable by this object then this object should report its maximum value (4,294,967,295) and myQoSPoliceMapConfMaxBandWidth must be used to set or report the Maximum bandwidth. 0 indicate that bandwidth will be not limitted.

myQoSPoliceMapConfBurstFlowLimit.name: myQoSPoliceMapConfBurstFlowLimit
myQoSPoliceMapConfBurstFlowLimit.description: Limit of burst traffic of this traffic classification in units of byte. 0 indicate that burst traffic will be not limitted.

myQoSPoliceMapConfExceedAction.name: myQoSPoliceMapConfExceedAction
myQoSPoliceMapConfExceedAction.description: The action deal with the traffic exceeded bandwidth.

myQoSPoliceMapConfExceedDscp.name: myQoSPoliceMapConfExceedDscp
myQoSPoliceMapConfExceedDscp.description: The new dscp value will replaces the old dscp value of packet when traffic of packet has exceeded bandwidth. This value has meaning only when value of myQoSPoliceMapConfExceedAction is 'modify-dscp' .

myQoSPoliceMapConfNewDscp.name: myQoSPoliceMapConfNewDscp
myQoSPoliceMapConfNewDscp.description: The new dscp value will replaces the old dscp value of packet regardless whether the traffic has exceeded bandwidth. Setting this value to -1 indicate that the dscp value of packet will not be modifed

myQoSPoliceMapCfgEntryStatus.name: myQoSPoliceMapCfgEntryStatus
myQoSPoliceMapCfgEntryStatus.description: Status of this entry, set this object to valid will creat a entry, and set its value to invalid will delete this entry.

myQoSPoliceMapConfMaxHighBandWidth.name: myQoSPoliceMapConfMaxHighBandWidth
myQoSPoliceMapConfMaxHighBandWidth.description: Maximum bandwidth of this traffic classification in units of kbps. 0 indicate that bandwidth will be not limitted. when myQoSPoliceMapConfMaxBandWidth is equal to ,this object display the real Maximum bandwidth of this traffic classification

myQosPoliceIfExtTable.name: myQosPoliceIfExtTable
myQosPoliceIfExtTable.description: list of QoS Police Map interface objects.

myIfInPoliceMapName.name: myIfInPoliceMapName
myIfInPoliceMapName.description: Police map name of this interface ingress match. It indicate that this interface doesn't match any ACL which this string is null

myIfOutPoliceMapName.name: myIfOutPoliceMapName
myIfOutPoliceMapName.description: Police map name of this interface egress match. It indicate that this interface doesn't match any ACL which this string is null

myQoSMIBCompliance.name: myQoSMIBCompliance
myQoSMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the My QoS MIB

myQoSPriorityMIBGroup.name: myQoSPriorityMIBGroup
myQoSPriorityMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects providing qos priority ability to a My agent.

myQoSTrafficClassMIBGroup.name: myQoSTrafficClassMIBGroup
myQoSTrafficClassMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects providing qos traffic classification ability to a My agent.
